entry.tran: 重复;雷同;翻版;老调重弹
entry.def: If you describe something as a rehash, you are criticizing it because it repeats old ideas, facts, or themes, though some things have been changed to make it appear new.

example.ex: The Observer found the play 'a feeble rehash of familiar Miller themes'...
example.tran: 《观察家报》认为这部剧“是大家熟悉的米勒式主题的拙劣翻版”。

example.ex: Most of the 'new' models promised by American car makers look set to be little more than rehashes of existing products.
example.tran: 这些美国汽车制造商承诺推出的“新款”多半都像是现有车型的翻版。

entry.tran: 对…改头换面;只作轻微改动地重复
entry.def: If you say that someone rehashes old ideas, facts, or accusations, you disapprove of the fact that they present them in a slightly different way so that they seem new or original.

example.ex: They've taken some of the best bits out of the best things and rehashed them...
example.tran: 他们从最好的东西中提取一些精华的部分，然后新瓶装旧酒。

example.ex: They are just bringing up all their old rehashed claims with no prospect or vision for the future.
example.tran: 他们只不过是在老调重弹，提出的声明中没有对未来的展望或设想。
